The paper deals with the problem of incorporating macro actions into the primitive action space to speed up the learning process in deep reinforcement learning. This topic is closely related to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), systems and control (cs.SY), and computer vision (cs.CV). However, given the focus on deep reinforcement learning and the use of genetic algorithms to construct macro actions, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories.
